===message:I am not quite sure how you came to believe that the North enslaved the South.  I am also not quite sure how you can believe that the North was blaming the South.  Yes, some people thought that the South should be punished for succeeding from the Union, but how did the North do this?  Slavery became a part of the Civil War after it had begun; the original beginnings of the Civil War came from the South and North’s mistrust of each other and the belief of states’ rights.  From my readings, I gained another view point.  I am interested to see how you gained these insights. 
