===subject:People or property?
===from:Michael E. Elbe
===email:csu16286@mail.claytonstate.net
===date:Mon Feb 17  9:59:18 2003
===message:Southern slave owners didn't view slaves as people, they saw them as property the same as a farmer views his cattle.  They saw slaves as a necessary means to manitain the aristocratic lifestyle to which they were accustomed.  However they felt that the North wanted to destroy this lifestyle by abolishing slavery, and was using political means to do this.  Southerners felt that the North was trying to "enslave" them by enacting laws prohibiting the expansion of slavery into the new western territories, and eventually abolishing slavery altogether.
=========yorg=========
